    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I added comments and addressed destruction.\n\nThe objects types using the secure_allocator are SecureString, CKeyingMaterial, and CPrivKey.  SecureString is used as a parameter to some functions that could be used during object construction (or could end up being used by someone else in the future).  It would be non-trivial to make sure these objects are not used in staticly constructed objects.  In the long run, I think the best solution is to eliminate all staticly-initialized objects entirely and instead explicitly create the objects at init and free them in shutdown.  If that's something you want, I can start working on that...\n",
