    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Managed instances are generally better practice than globally-contructed objects, as construct/destruct order isn't guaranteed between them. Also, if there are objects that have overhead in constructing, doing so lazily (=upon first use) is better for modularity (don't waste time/memory on stuff that a user of your code doesn't use).\n\nGeneral ACK on the idea, though I'd feel more comfortable if the page manager would also get destructed again. Do you know if there's a best-practice idiom for that?\n\nAlso needs rebase.\n",
