    "body": "> General ACK on the idea, though I'd feel more comfortable if the page manager would also get destructed again. Do you know if there's a best-practice idiom for that?\n\nFrom what I understand (about C++), local-statics are destructed in the reverse order they're constructed before program exit.  So the destructor is indeed called at exit.\n\nAlso, rebased.\n",
